author: Joe Garofoli
title: Washington state woman, 71, arrested in slaying of Rodeo woman
text:
A 71-year-old Washington state woman has been arrested in the shooting death of a 69-year-old Rodeo woman, authorities said Sunday.
More Bay Area news Morning showers to make way for Bay Area sunshine Things I learned after I moved to the San Francisco Bay Area Tiny Oakland house moves up the block from hospital Linda June Thomas was arrested by Contra Costa County Sheriffâ€™s Office deputies in connection with the death of a woman at a home on the 200 block of Garretson Ave. in Rodeo, said Jimmy Lee , director of public affairs for the department.
Responding to reports of a domestic disturbance call, law officers arrived on the scene at 12:30 a.m. Saturday and found the victim suffering from gunshot wounds. She was pronounced dead at the scene. Officials did not identify the victim pending notification of her family.
Deputies later arrested Thomas in connection with the killing. Anyone with information on the case is asked to call detectives at (925) 313-2600.
Joe Garofoli is a San Francisco Chronicle staff writer. E-mail: jgarofoli@sfchronicle.com Twitter: @joegarofoli
